                "text": "Watson PE, Watson ID, Batt RD. Total body water volumes for adult males and females estimated from simple anthropometric measurements. Am J Clin Nutr. 1980;33(1):27-39."
            }
        ],
        "evidence": "<p>Sodium deficit = total body water&nbsp;&times; (desired Na - pt's Na)</p>\n<p>For adults, total body water (TBW) is calculated using the Watson equation:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Men: TBW, liters = 2.447 &ndash; 0.09516&nbsp;&times; age, years + 0.1074&nbsp;&times; height, cm + 0.3362&nbsp;&times; weight, kg</li>\n<li>Women: TBW, liters = -2.097 + 0.1069&nbsp;&times; height, cm + 0.2466&nbsp;&times; weight, kg</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For children, TBW = 0.6 &times; weight, kg</p>",
        "facts": "<p>Remember not to correct too rapidly to avoid central pontine myelinolysis!</p>\n<p>The&nbsp;<calculator id=\"480\">hyponatremia correction rate calculator</calculator>&nbsp;can be used to pick an appropriate fluid and volume as well.</p>",
